{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "customer-service-tienda-generica",
		"name": "Customer Service — Tienda Genérica",
		"description": "# Customer Service API Documentation\n\n## Overview\nThe **customer-service** is a TypeScript microservice (port **3004**) responsible for full CRUD operations on customers within the Tienda Genérica backend system. It uses **Express 4** as the HTTP framework, **TypeORM 0.3** as the ORM, and **MySQL 8.0** (`db_customers` schema) as the database.\n\n## Architecture\n```\nHandler → Repository → Domain (Clean Architecture, no use-case layer)\n```\n\nThis service is **internal only** — it does **not** validate JWTs. All requests must pass through the **API Gateway** (port 8080), which validates the JWT and injects the following headers:\n\n| Header | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `X-User-Id` | Cédula of the authenticated user |\n| `X-Username` | Username of the authenticated user |\n| `X-Internal` | Always `\"true\"` when coming from gateway |\n\n## Standard Response Envelope\nEvery endpoint returns this structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true | false,\n  \"data\": { ... } | [ ... ] | null,\n  \"error\": null | \"Descriptive error message\"\n}\n```\n\n## Database Model — `customers` table\n| Column | Type | Constraints | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| cedula | VARCHAR(20) | PRIMARY KEY | National ID number |\n| full_name | VARCHAR(100) | NOT NULL | Full name |\n| address | VARCHAR(200) | NOT NULL | Customer address |\n| phone | VARCHAR(20) | NOT NULL | Phone number |\n| email | VARCHAR(100) | NOT NULL | Email address |\n| created_at | TIMESTAMP | AUTO (creation time) | Timestamp |\n\n## Business Rules\n1. `cedula` must be unique across all customers\n2. All fields (`cedula`, `full_name`, `address`, `phone`, `email`) are required for create and update operations\n3. `cedula` cannot be changed on update — it is the identifier\n4. The list endpoint always returns an array (`[]` if empty, never `null`)\n5. Delete returns 204 with no body content",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
